<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[295,015] s 4 Definitions">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4" type="ext"/>[295,015]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Definitions</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>4</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>In this Act, except in so far as the context or subject-matter otherwise indicates or requires:</text></p>
<deflist><defitem id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.COURT"><defterm><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.COURT" type="ext"/><emph typestyle="bf">Court</emph></defterm>   <defdesc>
<p><text>means:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.COURT.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.COURT.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>the Supreme Court of New South Wales; or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.COURT.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.COURT.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.DC.DCAN.S134B" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">section 134B</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the District Court Act 1973, and without affecting the jurisdictional limitations referred to in that section, the District Court of New South Wales; or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.COURT.C"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.COURT.C" type="ext"/>(c)</lilabel>
<p><text>in accordance with 
<remotelink dpsi="007R" refpt="CPPN.OLNSW.LCAN07.S32" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">section 32</remotelink>
 of the Local Court Act 2007, and without affecting the jurisdictional limitations referred to in that section, the Local Court; or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.COURT.D"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.COURT.D" type="ext"/>(d)</lilabel>
<p><text>in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.BSC89.S89D" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">section 89D</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the Home Building Act 1989, and without affecting the jurisdictional limitations referred to in that section, the Tribunal, or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.COURT.E"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.COURT.E" type="ext"/>(e)</lilabel>
<p><text>in accordance with section 123 of the Retirement Villages Act 1999, and without affecting the jurisdictional limitations referred to in that section, the Tribunal.</text></p>
</li>
</l></defdesc><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[def  am Act 122 of 1996   s 5 and Sch 7  ; Act 31 of 1999   s 3 and Sch 1  ; Act 81 of 2000   s 205 and Sch 3  ; Act 82 of 2001   s 90 and Sch 7 , effective 25 February 2002; Act No 28 of 2005   s 5.8 and Sch 5, effective 15 August 2005 ; Act 94 of 2007  s 3 and Sch 1.18, effective 6 July 2009]</text></p></leg:histnote></defitem></deflist>
<deflist><defitem id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.FAIR-TRADING-TRIBUNAL"><defterm><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.FAIR-TRADING-TRIBUNAL" type="ext"/><emph typestyle="bf">Fair Trading Tribunal</emph></defterm>  <leg:histnote>
<p><text>[def  rep Act 82 of 2001    s 90 and Sch 7, effective 25 February 2002]</text></p></leg:histnote></defitem></deflist>
<deflist><defitem id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.LAND-INSTRUMENT"><defterm><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.LAND-INSTRUMENT" type="ext"/><emph typestyle="bf">land instrument</emph></defterm>   <defdesc>
<p><text>means an instrument that transfers title to land, creates an estate or interest in land or is a dealing within the meaning of the 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.RPN" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">Real Property Act 1900</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 ;</text></p>
</defdesc></defitem></deflist>
<deflist><defitem id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.TRIBUNAL"><defterm><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.TRIBUNAL" type="ext"/><emph typestyle="bf">Tribunal</emph></defterm>  <defdesc>
<p><text>means the Consumer, Trader and Tenancy Tribunal established by the 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.CTTTAN01" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">Consumer, Trader and Tenancy Tribunal Act 2001</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 .</text></p>
</defdesc><leg:histnote>
<p><text>[def  insrt Act 82 of 2001    s 90 and Sch 7  , effective 25 February 2002]</text></p></leg:histnote></defitem></deflist>
<deflist><defitem id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.UNJUST"><defterm><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.1.UNJUST" type="ext"/><emph typestyle="bf">unjust</emph></defterm>   <defdesc>
<p><text>includes unconscionable, harsh or oppressive; and <defterm><emph typestyle="bf">injustice</emph></defterm>   shall be construed in a corresponding manner.</text></p>
</defdesc></defitem></deflist>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A reference in this Act to a corporation does not include a reference to:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.2.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.2.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>an owners corporation constituted under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.SSMN96.S11" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">section 11</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the Strata Schemes Management Act 1996; or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.2.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.2.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>a corporation owning an interest in land and having a memorandum or articles of association conferring on owners of shares in the corporation the right to occupy certain parts of a building erected on that land,</text></p>
</li>
</l>
<p><text>all or the majority of which lots or parts, as the case may be, are intended to be occupied as dwellings.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subs (2)  am Act 139 of 1996    s 4 and Sch 2]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Notes included in this Act do not form part of this Act.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subs (3)  insrt Act 51 of 2010    s 2 and Sch 2[1], effective 1 July 2010]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTES"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S4.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTES</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.295015-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[295,015.5] &#x201c;Court&#x201d;">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [295,015.5] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_ACT_1980-16" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Contracts Review Act 1980</remotelink> s 7(1)(a).</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_ACT_2007-93" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Local Court Act 2007</remotelink> s 32.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.295015-5" type="ext"/>[295,015.5] </edpnum><title>&#x201c;Court&#x201d;</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The Local Court only has the power to grant relief under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.CRA.S7.1.A" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">s 7(1)(a)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 of the Contracts Review Act, and only if application for the exercise of the jurisdiction is made in proceedings concerning the contract that are in the course of being heard in the Local Court: LCA 2007 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.S32" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">s 32</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
. In other words, the Local Court only has jurisdiction, in the course of proceedings concerning the contract that are in the course of being heard in the Local Court, to decide to refuse to enforce any or all of the provisions of the contract.</text></p>
<p>
<text>Clause 5 of the Civil Procedure Act 2005 does not limit or increase the jurisdiction of any Court under the Act. </text></p>
</bodytext>
</level><level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.295015-10" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[295,015.10] &#x201c;Unjust&#x201d;"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.295015-10" type="ext"/>[295,015.10] </edpnum><title>&#x201c;Unjust&#x201d;</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>&#x201c;The definition of 'unjust' is not exclusive. It is in my opinion a mistake to think that a contract or one of its terms is only unjust when it is unconscionable, harsh or oppressive. Any contract or contractual provision, not excluded from the operation of the Act and which the court considers is unjust in the circumstances existing at the time it was made may be the subject of relief under the Act&#x201d;: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1986"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000248" spanref="cr000248-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="5"/><ci:page num="610"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000248" spanref="cr000248-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="620" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr000249" spanref="cr000249-003" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ConvR"/><ci:page num="55-306"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">West v AGC (Advances) Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000248-001">(1986) 5 NSWLR 610</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000248-002" status="unval">at 620&#x2013;1</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr000249-003" status="unval">NSW ConvR ¶55-306</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> per McHugh JA.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
