</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S5"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[295,020] s 5 Act binds Crown">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S5" type="ext"/>[295,020]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Act binds Crown</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>5</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>This Act binds the Crown not only in right of New South Wales but also, so far as the legislative power of Parliament permits, the Crown in all its other capacities.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S6"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="sect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SECT" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[295,025] s 6 Certain restrictions on grant of relief">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S6" type="ext"/>[295,025]</edpnum><title searchtype="SECT-TITLE">Certain restrictions on grant of relief</title><desig searchtype="SECT-NUM"><designum>6</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S6.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S6.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The Crown, a public or local authority or a corporation may not be granted relief under this Act.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S6.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subsect" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBSECT">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S6.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A person may not be granted relief under this Act in relation to a contract so far as the contract was entered into in the course of or for the purpose of a trade, business or profession carried on by the person or proposed to be carried on by the person, other than a farming undertaking (including, but not limited to, an agricultural, pastoral, horticultural, orcharding or viticultural undertaking) carried on by the person or proposed to be carried on by the person wholly or principally in New South Wales.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subs (2)  am Act 121 of 1996    s 3 and Sch 3]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.CRA.S6.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.295025-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[295,025.5]">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [295,025.5] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_ACT_1980-16" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Contracts Review Act 1980</remotelink> s 6(2).</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.295025-5" type="ext"/>[295,025.5] </edpnum></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>Where the proprietors of a company give a guarantee to secure the debts of the company which carries on business, such proprietors are not prevented by the section from seeking relief under the section because it is the company rather than themselves which is carrying on the business: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1985"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000250" spanref="cr000250-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:page num="145"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Toscano v Holland Securities Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000250-001">(1985) 1 NSWLR 145</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>  ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1985"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000251" spanref="cr000251-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="3"/><ci:page num="174"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Australian Bank Ltd v Stokes</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000251-001">(1985) 3 NSWLR 174</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>  ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1984"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000252" spanref="cr000252-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="NSWConvR,"/><ci:page num="55-212"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000252" spanref="cr000252-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="57" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Collins v Parker</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000252-001" status="unval">(1984) NSW Conv R 55&#x2013;212</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000252-002" status="unval">at 57,469</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite>  ; <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1991"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000253" spanref="cr000253-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="ASC"/><ci:page num="56-097"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref anaphref="cr000253" spanref="cr000253-002" status="unval"><ci:pinpoint num="57" targettype="page"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Coombs v Bahama Palm Trading Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000253-001" status="unval">(1991) ASC ¶56-097</ci:span> <ci:span spanid="cr000253-002" status="unval">at 57,025</ci:span></citefragment></ci:content></ci:cite> . However, the section refers to a contract entered into &#x201c;in the course of&#x201d; or &#x201c;for the purpose of&#x201d; a business carried on by the applicant. For an instance where the court found that loans had been entered into by persons with limited understanding of English who had no connection with the bank involved, all transactions being carried out through their son, the loan being for the son's business, they not being involved in the business at all, see <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr000254" spanref="cr000254-001"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200301234"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">St George Bank Ltd v Trimarchi</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [2003] NSWSC 151; <ci:span spanid="cr000254-001"> BC200301234</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="360676" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>  . It was accordingly held that the applicants were not excluded from seeking relief by virtue of 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.CRA.S6.2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">s 6(2)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 .</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
